args: I've gathered everyone like you asked,\nZena. Go ahead.
I have kept something from you all\nin regard to the Lambentree ritual.
I have already performed the rite\nback in my own world.
I failed. The Other's fell power tainted the\nLambentree, and the result was...horrific.
I cannot say what might happen here\nshould I attempt the rite again.
Which is why you have been training\nwith such vigor, I assume.
Yes. But I felt that if I told you about this,\nyou wouldn't trust me to perform the rite.
Which would remove my only opportunity\nto earn a true place among you.
This was selfish of me, and I apologize.\nI understand now that I should have told\nyou the complete truth straightaway.
Well, thank you for doing so now, Zena.\n...Elly? What do you think.
I understand her concerns, but there's no\ntelling what ill might come of NOT doing\nthe rite, either.
And while there are records of the rite not\nbeing performed in the Auspex's absence,\nit has never been skipped while one exists.
If we fail to perform it now, I fear Zethia\nwill go down in history as the first of her\nstation to so neglect her duties.
She wanted to serve as the Auspex above\nall other things. To fail like that...
Considering all of those factors, I believe\nthe conclusion is clear: We will continue\nentrusting the task to Zena.
You just need to get control over the\nOther's power, yeah?
You will have the entire Halidom's support\nin this. I shall begin by gathering those\nskilled in the manipulation of mana.
Zena, if you prove unable to control the\nOther's power by the day of the rite,\nI'm afraid we'll have to cancel it...
I understand—and I won't let you down.
You're the only one who can\nsave this world, Zena.
And I shall. I swear to you all, I will\nperfect my control over the Other's power\nin time for the Lambentree rite!
Perhaps if you unleashed\nyour mana in stages?
When released all at once, the resistance\nfrom the Other's power is too great.
Yes, I see. I will give it a try!
Seems like Zena's out of her funk.
And she's hanging out with people again,\nwhich is great to see.
Nice hustle out there, Zena!\nHow you feeling?
I've received advice from so many people\nlately and feel close to a breakthrough.
That would never have been the case\nwere it not for you two.
Aw, shucks! We didn't do nothin'.
But you did, at least to me—\nit was extremely special.
I had given up; abandoned any hope of\nbeing dear to another, independent of my\nusefulness to them.
I've been called a traitor in some worlds,\na murderer in others. And somewhere\nalong the way, I came to believe it.
Okay, these other-world people sound like\nhuge jerkfaces! You were taken over by\nan ancient DEMON for the love'a cake!
And it performed atrocities using this body;\nI can't blame them for feeling as they did.

At first, I suffered. Then came despair,
and after that, a grim acceptance that I
would ever be the villain in any world
unfortunate enough to host me.
I thought the only reason you all treated\nme with such kindness was because you\nsaw me as Zethia's replacement.

Which is why I felt the only way to hold
onto my place here was to make myself
a useful pawn in whatever scheme you
required of me.
Looking back on it now, I am ashamed.\nForgive me for assuming the worst of you.

Forgiven! And seriously, I like this new,
chipper you a LOT more than the glum
chum you were earlier. I think dropping
that whole ＂I'm evil＂ idea works for you.
Ha ha, I expect it does. I feel close to an\nanswer now—I know it is within reach.
The day of the rite draws close, and I will\nhave it mastered, whatever it takes!
The day before the Lambentree rite...
How is Zena? Will she be ready?
Zena, will you be ready by tomorrow?
Maybe it's best to call the rite off.
No! If it isn't performed, calamity will\nbefall the world!
Watching a friend tear herself apart over\nthis feels pretty calamitous to me...

We all know how hard you tried, Zena.
No one's gonna blame you if this thing
can't be pulled off. I mean, stuff happens,
ya know? We're still good.
And don't think for a moment that it\nthreatens your place here among us.
(It's true that I pushed myself in order\nto justify my worth here at first.)
(This isn't for my own sake anymore; it is\nfor this world, and I want to do all I can.)
(As the Auspex, I seek to protect this world\nthrough the power of prayer.)
(This is the same feeling as back then;\nI feel I've remembered something vital\nto an Auspex I'd long since forgotten...)
(The Auspex is a pure being, and her\nmana won't respond to a tainted heart.)
(But now that I've reclaimed this pure\ndesire, perhaps...)
Please give me one final chance.
Well, I certainly won't stop you, but...
More... Still more! Use your mana\nto quell the power of the Other!
There! Now, just like that...\nrelease the mana's flow!
Holy freakin' casserole, she did it...\nZENAAAA! YOU DID IIIIIT!
I'm ready to attempt the rite! I can do this.\nFor the world, for all of you, and for Zethia!
This time, I will see my duties through!
